Does this work with galaxy ? Yes it will work with any android or any iPhone well. How do I charge the battery pack? Do I need to purchase a different cord? You may recharge the powerbank via its attached recharging cord, or you may get a seperated A to C or C to C cable to recharge the powerbank. Can this portable charger be transported on an aircraft? Power banks must be carried in carry-on baggage only, can not been carried in checked bags Does this support PD/QC fast charging? No, It does not support pd or qc quick charging. This is a basic 5V-2A & 5V-3A power bank, it's only faster than 5V-1A or 5V-1.5A powerbank. How much time it will take to fully recharged the power bank Normally, it will take 4.5-6 hours to fully recharegd the powerbank. But please make sure your charger block and also your charging cable is 15 watts or above. If you use your own 5w iPhone wall charger, then it will charge powerbank quite slowly.

reviews.reviewTitle: It has become a staple on the kitchen table during family gatherings
reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. The idea was to have a practical solution for charging our devices, especially when the family is visiting and there is always someone squatting at the kitchen table. I have to say that this charger really lived up to my expectations. We can do three large phone charges with a single charge of the device, which is perfect for busy days.It has become a staple on the kitchen table during family gatherings. The overall quality of the product is excellent. The capacity provides reliable power, and the outputs are a godsend, especially when everyone wants to plug in their phones at the same time. The charging speed is also impressive.On the strengths side, the versatility with the different integrated cables is a big advantage. One can charge almost any device without having to worry about bringing extra cables. However, the only downside I noted is the slightly heavier weight than some portable chargers, but that's an acceptable compromise given its performance. A handy tip would be to always charge the device overnight to ensure it is ready for use the next day. It solved the problem of scattered cables and contested power outlets during family gatherings.
